text.tspan: Training computation vs. parameters in notable AI systems, by domain
Computation is measured in total petaFLOP, which is 10¹⁵ floating-point operations. Parameters are variables in an
AI system whose values are adjusted during training to establish how input data gets transformed into the desired
Note: Each domain's training data has a specific unit; for example, for vision it is images and for language it is words. This means systems can
only be compared directly within the same domain.
